Black Walnut Cake
  --FireInMiSoul1 (imgur)

1/2 c butter or margarine, softened
1/2 c shortening
2 c sugar
5 eggs, separated
1 c buttermilk
1 tsp baking soda
2 c ap flour
1 tsp vanilla
1 c black walnutsm chopped
1/2 tsp cream of tartar

Cream butter and shortening, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine buttermilk and baking soda, stir until baking soda dissolves. Add flour to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Mix after each addition. Stir in vanjilla, add 1 c of walnuts, stirring well. Beat egg whites (at room temp) and cream of tartar until stiff peak forms, fold into batter. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9" round pans. Bake at 350F for 22-25 min or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans; let cool completely. 


Cream Cheese Frosting:
3/4 c butter, softened
8 oz cream cheese, softened
6 c powdered sugar
1 tsp vanilla

Crean butter and cheese gradually; add sugar, beating until smooth and fluffy; stir in vanilla. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

